entry.title: Onboard vs. Ground Recording
entry.summary:
The main video is recorded using a FatShark HD1. The small video is recorded using a JXD990 directly connected to the video receiver. The Fatshark produces a much better video, despite the odd colors and the defocused lens.
The fatshark records 1280x720 8Mbit/s The JXD990 records 704x448 4Mbit/s
both have a lousy encoder, I have seen 4Mbit/s videos that looked magnitudes better.
Maybe I will go for the GOPRO HERO HD.
Update: the HD1 is now broken, due to its bad construction, I now use the GoPro HD which is MUCH better.
